# Optional: Google Drive sync ("Sign in with Google" in the top bar).
# Without this, the app still works fully — data is just saved locally in the
# browser instead of the user's Google Drive.
#
# How to get this value:
#   1. Google Cloud Console → create/select a project.
#   2. APIs & Services → Enable APIs → enable "Google Drive API".
#   3. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → OAuth client ID.
#        - Application type: Web application
#        - Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:3000 (and your prod URL)
#   4. Copy the Client ID below. There is NO client secret for this browser flow.
#
# The scope used is drive.file (non-sensitive), so no Google app verification is
# required and there is no user cap.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
